`template/` is the scaffold a new project's repo is bootstrapped from: it supplies the CI/lint check suite, the merge-driver wiring for `.context/` files, and (implicitly, via `scripts/update-template.sh`) the mechanism for pulling upstream template updates into a downstream project after the fact. Depending on this directory means a downstream project gets a working `.context/` merge policy plus a pass/fail CI gate, both designed to be refreshed in place rather than hand-maintained.

The two children are only loosely coupled today: `.gitattributes` declares the `ctx-regenerate` merge driver for `.context/**/*.ctx` and `rollup.ctx`, but that driver has no implementation yet anywhere in this tree — conflicts must currently be resolved by hand via `ctx-resummarize`. `scripts/` is the enforcement side (lint/CI checks) and the self-update mechanism; it knows nothing about the merge-driver gap. If the driver is ever implemented, it will presumably live under `scripts/` or be invoked by `update-template.sh`, at which point the two children become directly coupled — that link doesn't exist yet.

Invariant spanning both: anything matching `.context/**/*.ctx` or `.context/**/rollup.ctx` is claimed by `.gitattributes` as merge-driver territory regardless of whether `scripts/` (or anything else in the template) actually provides that driver — so adding new `.ctx`-producing tooling anywhere in a downstream project doesn't require touching this directory, but implementing the driver does.

intent_divergence: no intent.md exists for this directory, so no stated intent to check against.